        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &quot;Subsidized Scheme for Widows&quot; by the Women &amp; Child Development Department, Haryana Government, aims to provide financial assistance to Haryana-domiciled widows, divorced, and Legally Separated Women. Through this scheme, a subsidy on the total loan is provided. The scheme is covered without collateral security by the bank. The scheme is implemented by the Haryana Women Development Corporation.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n1. A 25% flat subsidy, subject to a maximum of ₹50,000/-, will be provided on the total loan (not as a capital subsidy).\n1. The beneficiary&#39;s share is 10% of the total loan.\n1. The maximum loan limit is ₹3,00,000/-.\n1. The scheme will be covered under without collateral security by the bank.\n1. The balance amount will be covered from commercial/nationalised banks.\n\n<br>\n\n> **Mode of Disbursement:** The balance amount will be covered from commercial/nationalised banks.\n\n> **Moratorium Period:** The moratorium period will be three months after disbursement of the loan.\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "\n1. No subsidy for interest accrued on a delayed period will be allowed in case of default of payment of EMI.\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to provide financial assistance to Haryana Domiciled Widow, Divorced, and Legally Separated Women. Through this scheme, a subsidy on the total loan is provided.",
